The check_update plugin incorrectly generates an error when a default value is added to a leaf for a defined type. Simple scenario that illustrates this is shown below, adding the default value to the leaf generates an error even though f_type does not have an implicit default value. I believe the issue is here:

https://github.com/mbj4668/pyang/blob/master/pyang/plugins/check_update.py#L521

The check for "oldtype.i_typedef.i_default_str is not None" appears to be incorrect, it should be checking "oldtype.i_typedef.i_default is not None". 

