pyang 2.2.1
PMERLO-M-T00T:~ pmerlo$ pyang --check-update-from=f.yang f@2014-04-01.yang
f@2014-04-01.yang:17: error: the leaf had an implicit default

f.yang:
module f {
  namespace "urn:f";
  prefix f;

  typedef f_type {
      type enumeration {
          enum "foo";
          enum "bar";
      }
  }

  container b {
    leaf q {
      type f_type;
    }
  }
}

f@2014-04-01.yang
module f {
  namespace "urn:f";
  prefix f;

  revision 2014-04-01;

  typedef f_type {
      type enumeration {
          enum "foo";
          enum "bar";
      }
  }

  container b {
    leaf q {
      type f_type;
      default "foo";
    }
  }
}

The YANG shown at the bottom generates the output shown below for the `address1` and `address2` leaf nodes.

It looks to me as though the `select_quote()` function is calling `need_quote()` to determine whether to use single quotes rather than the preferred double quotes. But I don't think this is the right criterion: spaces in the string are causing it to use single quotes for `address1`'s first line (the only difference between `address1` and `address2` is the spaces surrounding the equals sign).

```
    leaf address1 {
      description
        "YANG input uses single quotes. YANG output retains single quotes
         for line 1 and uses double quotes for line 2.";
      type leafref {
        path '../../interface[name = current()/../ifname]'
           + "/address/ip";
      }
    }
```
